caption.text:
@filmores.gentlemens.club was the first adult entertainment club I ever went to. I chose Filmores because I always loved the anticipation of passing by the building on the Dundas streetcar whenever I was heading out the east end and seeing how the sign had changed since the last time. 

I went in wondering if a friend I knew was working that night and if I‚Äôd run into them. The DJ was hounding the patrons in the front row of the stage for not tipping the dancers and saying, ‚ÄúWhat is this National Geographic, there‚Äôs a bunch of hyenas in the crowd tonight‚Äù. 

I remember who gave me my first lap dance. It was my birthday. My friends scrounged up some cash for me and another friend to go for a dance. I picked out a dancer covered in tattoos. All I remember was her saying, ‚ÄúYou can touch me anywhere but my pussy‚Äù. The rest went by quickly.

It‚Äôs not just Filmores, it‚Äôs that Toronto is consistently losing places that gives the city character and charm. People in my life know how much I love this city yet it is increasingly harder and harder to stay living as a working class artist. 

I love learning about the history of the city‚Äôs taboo sexual underworld and collecting items from this past. Even moreso now that @kiwithestripp3r has been in my personal life. 

The closing of Filmores is a big sad moment for many, grateful to have some cherished memories of the club while it was around.

PS, this poster is actually addressed to ‚ÄúDavid‚Äù, has been in my collection for a couple of years now and is current l not for sale.

caption.text:
Power outage update (2/1, 9 PM):

I‚Äôm deeply concerned by what residents are experiencing right now. While operations are being described as ‚Äúongoing,‚Äù neighbors are reporting no Con Edison staff on site and a loss of power following generator installation. That gap between what‚Äôs being said and what‚Äôs happening on the ground is unacceptable.

We need clear answers: when will the two temporary generators be fully operational and restoring power to all impacted residents? Which addresses remain without service? And what immediate support is available for non-NYCHA residents who are currently without heat and power while repairs continue? We are grateful to know the NYCHA buildings have full temporary power.

With freezing temperatures and real risks to families, children, seniors, and buildings, I am demanding more frequent and transparent updates from both NYC Emergency Management and Con Edison ahead of the Monday 2/2, 9 AM elected‚Äô follow-up. Our community deserves better.

If you‚Äôre impacted, please file a claim with Con Edison and notify my office so we can escalate cases and hold them accountable. Send to District39@council.nyc.gov.

caption.text:
Get ready for DJ LK - aka Laura Kelly - to play a sentimental swan song, set of all sets, at Slow Dance 2026! üåπ

For those that don‚Äôt know, Laura is the founder and organizer of Slow Dance. Though many people have worked on this event, every single year, she has been the driving force behind bringing everyone together. After 17 years, this is the last time Laura will be running Slow Dance‚ÄºÔ∏è Though it‚Äôs time for her to focus on new creative projects, she hopes a new generation of organizers will carry on the event in the future. As nothing is guaranteed after this year, let‚Äôs treat this Slow Dance like it could be our last! It‚Äôs going to be an incredibly meaningful night. Come and help commemorate 17 years of Laura running this community event by dancing like wild to her all vinyl DJ set ‚ù§Ô∏è

caption.text:
As of 11 PM on 2/1, I sent a letter to Timothy Cawley, CEO of Con Edison.

New Yorkers shouldn‚Äôt pay for failure. I‚Äôm calling on Con Edison to automatically suspend billing and issue full credits for this outage‚Äîno applications, no hoops.

Credits must reflect the real harm caused, including days without power, heat, and hot water, and be clearly explained in plain language.

caption.text:
#nowplaying: New Medieval by Levi J. Burr

Released just days ago, New Medieval is an instrumental journey through fingerstyle guitar, ambient textures, and subtle percussion. Inspired by that unsettling feeling that history has a habit of looping back on itself, the record drifts through echoes of old myths, modern unrest, and the strange comfort of familiar patterns.

Levi is a versatile and adventurous Australian musician, blending country blues, ambient, and fingerstyle guitar into tranquil, dreamlike pastoral soundscapes.

@levi.j.burr_music
levijburr.bandcamp.com
levijburr.com

#ambient #fingerstyle #guitar #folk

caption.text:
Bitondo Pizzeria is a long-standing pizza institution in Toronto‚Äôs Little Italy, located at 11 Clinton St, Toronto, ON M6J 2N7, Canada. For decades it‚Äôs been a go-to spot for locals and visitors craving hearty, old-school Italian pizza, panzerotti, sandwiches, and more. Ôøº  Bitondo has built a reputation on classic, nostalgic pizza and panzerotti ‚Äî comfort food done right with a focus on tradition rather than trends. The slices are generous, the cheese is melty, and the sauce has that familiar, satisfying flavour that keeps people coming back. Reviewers often point out the huge, cheesy slices and the cheesy panzerotti as crowd-pleasers.  Beyond pizza and panzerotti, the menu also includes Italian sandwiches (like veal and meatball), pastas, and sides ‚Äî making it a solid choice whether you want lunch, dinner, or a casual bite simply to enjoy with friends.  The menu stays true to its roots with favourites like:
	‚Ä¢	Classic pizzas (cheese, pepperoni, deluxe combinations)
	‚Ä¢	Panzerotti (often described as indulgently cheesy)
	‚Ä¢	Sandwiches (veal, chicken, meatball)
	‚Ä¢	Pasta dishes and sides
	‚Ä¢	Pizza by the slice
Drinks are simple and refreshing to wash down the rich flavours.  Inside, Bitondo‚Äôs vibe is casual and welcoming, with a bit of that retro charm reminiscent of pizza shops from earlier decades. While the d√©cor isn‚Äôt fancy, it adds to the authentic, no-frills experience.  Many loyal customers describe Bitondo as a Toronto classic ‚Äî a place they‚Äôve visited for years, sometimes since childhood. Its long history in Little Italy and consistent quality have helped it maintain a dedicated following. Ôøº Some diners love the place for its nostalgic feel and comforting food, while others note that quality and style can vary ‚Äî typical of older family-run eateries that prioritize tradition over modernization.

carousel_media.accessibility_caption: In a recent interview with @connorstorrieofficial, @sethmeyers referred to the name of Connor‚Äôs hometown‚ÄîOdessa, Texas‚Äîas being of Russian origin. It is important to set the record straight: Odesa is a historic Ukrainian city. While the name is shared, the roots are Ukrainian‚Äîa reality made even more poignant as the city of Odesa faces relentless daily bombardment from Russian forces at this very moment.

caption.text: During his interview with Connor Storrie on @latenightseth @sethmeyers asked the star of "Heated Rivalry" about his hometown ‚Äî Odessa, Texas. Meyers proceeded to claim that the city‚Äôs name is of Russian origin. However, that is utterly untrue, as Odesa is a Ukrainian city that continues to be heavily bombed by Russia every single day, maybe even the very moment you‚Äôre reading this.

caption.text:
Roast Gochujang Butter Cabbage w/ Kimchi Rice & Chilli Vinegar

Serves 2

Ingredients

For the kimchi steamed rice
75g kimchi
2 tsp soy sauce
1 tsp rice wine vinegar
1 teaspoon gochujang
200 short grain rice, rinsed well
2 tsp sesame oil

For the cabbage
1 hispi cabbage, halved lengthways through the base
1 tbsp gochujang
2 tbsp butter, plant based for vegan, room temperature
Salt

For the chilli vinegar (this will keep for a long time)
3 red chillies, seeds removed and roughly chopped
1-2 cloves garlic, peeled
300ml vinegar of choice
1 tbsp sugar

Garnish
Spring onions, finely shredded and placed in cold water to curl up
Sesame seeds

Method

Cook rice | Preheat the oven to 200¬∫C | Add the kimchi, soy sauce, rice wine vinegar, gochujang, rinsed rice, and 250ml water to a saucepan over a medium heat until simmering | Cover with a lid, turn down to very low and steam for 12 minutes | Remove the lid, turn the rice over, recover with the lid and leave to steam off the heat while you finish the rest

Cook cabbage | Combine the gochujang and butter well | Spread the gochujang butter over the cut side of the cabbage | Heat an oven proof frying pan over a medium high heat until hot | Add the cabbage, cut side down for a few minutes until golden and a little charred | Flip the cabbage so it‚Äôs cut side up, add about 100ml water to the pan and baste the cabbage a few times | Add to the oven and roast for 15 minutes until golden, tender and the sauce has reduced a little | Baste the cabbage with the glaze and sprinkle in a little sugar if needed for sweetness

Make chilli vinegar | While the cabbage is roasting, grind the garlic well in a pestle and mortar, then add the chilli and grind coarsely | Add the vinegar, salt and sugar, taste and adjust | Alternatively, blitz everything in a blender

Serve | Plate up the rice, cabbage, spooning over additional glaze, spring onions and a little of the chilli vinegar | Garnish with sesame seeds and enjoy

caption.text:
That black on your onions isn‚Äôt dirt ‚Äî it‚Äôs a fungus called Aspergillus niger that thrives in humid storage conditions.

Many home cooks mistake the black, powdery residue found on onion skins for simple garden dirt. 

In reality, this substance is Aspergillus niger, a common fungus that develops after harvest when onions are stored in high-humidity environments with poor airflow.

 While it primarily affects the dry, papery outer layers, identifying this mold correctly is the first step in ensuring your kitchen prep remains safe and your produce lasts longer.

The safety of the onion depends on how deep the fungus has reached. If the black spots are confined to the outer skin, you can simply peel away the affected layers and use the firm, odor-free bulb inside. However, if the onion has become soft, slimy, or develops a noticeable smell, it must be discarded immediately. It is a common misconception that heat solves the problem; while cooking may kill the fungus itself, it does not reliably eliminate the harmful mycotoxins that can linger within the vegetable.

source: University of California Agriculture and Natural Resources. (2023). Onion: Black Mold (Aspergillus niger). Statewide Integrated Pest Management Program.

caption.text:
Tom Verlaine's Jazzmaster Mods: Unique & Mysterious

thanks to @jimmyrip (who brought me this to restore and make it "stage-ready") I had the honor of going under the hood of Tom Verlaine's 1965 Jazzmaster which was both a fascinating and also validating experience. Despite being a legend, he struggled with his offsets and modded them just like the rest of us! While some of his solutions were flawed in execution, they made perfect sense with what he was trying to do (like wrapping his pickups in copper foil tape to attempt to address the awful buzzy 60 cycle hum thats inherent with those big ol Jazzmaster single coils!) or maybe messing with a pickups orientation and perhaps reverse polarity? In order to perhaps make it better cut through a mix? Definitely let me know if you might have any clues to help solve some of these mysteries. These of course, are only assumptions, we can never know for certain now as Tom left us too soon 3 years ago. In dedication to Tom and his incredible music, his undeniable influence and legacy which has and will continue to inspire so many of us for ages to come.

#jazzmaster #fenderjazzmaster #offsetguitars #tomverlaine #totallywiredguitars

caption.text:
Football goalkeepers wear sticky gloves during matches for control and safety. The grip looks unusual, so you might think it breaks the rules. 

Football laws allow these gloves. The stickiness comes from latex on the palm, not glue or added substances. A football travels at high speed and changes direction because of spin. Bare hands struggle to hold the ball, especially in rain, sweat, or cold weather. Gloves increase friction between the hand and the ball. This helps you catch cleanly instead of pushing the ball away. 

Fewer rebounds mean fewer second chances for attackers. Gloves also protect fingers and wrists from repeated impact. Because they improve control without creating unfair advantage, sticky gloves remain standard for football goalkeepers.

Credits: @loris_gk

#football #goalkeeper #goalkeepergloves #innovation

caption.text:
50 30 | S2 EP. 5 SPICY PEANUT CHICKEN NOODLES üçúüí™üçó

50g Protein | 676 Cal | 26 Fat | 60 Carbs

INGREDIENTS FOR 2

For the miso peanut sauce
40g peanut butter
25g white miso
20ml rice vinegar
20ml soy sauce
1 tbsp sugar
¬Ω tsp MSG (optional)
65ml water

For the herb salad
¬Ω cucumber
10g fresh coriander
4 spring onions

For the spicy chicken
1 garlic cloves
1 tbsp gochujang
1 tbsp Korean chilli flakes
1 tbsp dark soy sauce
1 tbsp rice vinegar
1 tbsp sugar
400g chicken mince
1 tbsp vegetable oil

To serve
200g udon noodles

METHOD
To make the miso peanut sauce, whisk together the peanut butter, white miso, rice vinegar, soy sauce, sugar and MSG until smooth. Slowly drizzle in the water while whisking until the sauce is velvety and pourable. Set aside.
For the herb salad, slice the cucumber into thin half moons, pick the coriander leaves and finely slice the green tops of the spring onions. Combine in a bowl. Chill in iced water if you want more crunch.

Add the garlic, gochujang, Korean chilli flakes, dark soy, rice vinegar, sugar and the white parts of the spring onions to a blender. Blitz until smooth and set aside.

Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Add the oil, then the chicken mince. Press it flat and let it brown deeply on one side before breaking it up. Cook through, then pour in the chilli sauce. Stir and let it bubble for 2‚Äì3 minutes until thick, sticky and fully coating the chicken.

Cook the noodles according to pack instructions. Drain and toss immediately with the miso peanut sauce and a splash of warm noodle water until glossy and well coated.

Divide the saucy noodles between bowls. Top with the spicy chicken and the herb salad. Finish with extra miso peanut sauce if you like.

This Leopard go-kart was built by Lewis Engineering of Alliance, Ohio, and purchased by the seller in 2021, who tells us he believes it is pre-production prototype. The kart was refurbished under current ownership and features a two-piece tubular chromoly frame finished in bronze and a 5.8ci West Bend 580 single-cylinder engine linked to a centrifugal clutch and drive chain. It's listed now with no reserve on BaT! 

Equipment includes a single seat trimmed with leopard-style printed vinyl, a three-spoke steering wheel, a drum brake, a Palmini chrome seat-back fuel tank, 6‚Ä≥ GoPower wheels, an aluminum floor pan, and a Tillotson carburetor. Tap the @bringatrailer linkinbio to see the full listing before it closes Tuesday.

caption.text:
Two newly released emails from the Epstein files have reignited debate over material that was long dismissed by the media as baseless conspiracy.

‚ÄúPizzagate‚Äù was a theory that emerged during the 2016 election cycle, alleging that powerful political and financial figures were using coded language in emails to discuss illegal activity involving children. The theory centered on repeated references to ‚Äúpizza‚Äù and related terms, which critics mocked as absurd and used to discredit anyone who questioned the emails. Major media outlets and tech platforms labeled the theory false and shut down further discussion.

The newly released Epstein emails include messages referencing ‚Äúpizza‚Äù in unusual contexts. In one email, a sender asks Epstein, ‚ÄúMay I bring in your slice of pizza to you?‚Äù In another, a separate message reads, ‚ÄúAlert ‚Äì Send pizza to Bobby!!‚Äù These are not online rumors but emails taken directly from official Epstein-related files, raising fresh questions about language that was previously dismissed without examination.

caption.text:
Abraham Poincheval‚Äôs performance at the Palais de Tokyo in Paris was an extreme study in isolation and sensory deprivation. For seven consecutive days, he remained sealed inside a 12-ton limestone block that had been carved exactly to the dimensions of his sitting body. There was zero room to turn or stand, effectively turning the artist into a literal internal component of the sculpture.

The technical reality of this life-support system was minimal: a small air vent for oxygen and a limited supply of dried food and water. Every heartbeat and movement was monitored as a technical part of the exhibit, testing the psychological limits of the human mind when stripped of all external stimuli. By merging his physical body with the immovable stone, Poincheval forced a confrontation between the fleeting human form and the geological permanence of the limestone.

caption.text:
One device is thrown away.
The other becomes pure gold. ‚ú®

This breakdown exposes the real difference between electronic waste and industrial recovery. What looks like simple dismantling is actually a precise system of separation, chemical processing, and material refinement.

Components are removed.
Metals are isolated.
Gold is extracted.
Impurities are eliminated.
Every step is calculated to recover maximum value from discarded technology.

In modern industry, nothing is truly waste.
It is transformed.

This comparison makes it painfully clear why advanced recycling is not about disposal ‚Äî it is about rebuilding resources for the future.

caption.text:
Opening this Thursday 5th February at @nicklegalleries 5pm

ùôíùôùùôÆ ùòøùô§ùô£‚Äôùô© ùôîùô§ùô™‚Ä¶ simultaneously a question and invitation, is borrowed from Diana Veerland‚Äôs 1936 fashion column for Harpers Bizarre, which consisted of imaginative suggestions and advice: Why don‚Äôt you‚Ä¶ have all your dogs in bright yellow collars and leads like all the dogs in Paris? Why don‚Äôt you‚Ä¶ have every room done up in every colour green? A m√©lange of plants, green glass, green porcelains‚Ä¶. Why don‚Äôt you‚Ä¶ Find one dress that you like and have it copied many times?

Drawing on this ethos of suggestion and participation, ùôíùôùùôÆ ùòøùô§ùô£‚Äôùô© ùôîùô§ùô™‚Ä¶curated by Michele Hardy and Jenelle Pasiechnik is an exhibition of the works I‚Äôve made over the last decade that includes processes of printmaking, video, costume, sculpture, ceramics, quilting and rug hooking. 

Featuring: Dark Horse (2016), Gift-love (2019), Harmonia (2021), Bad Press (2022), Quilts of Canada (2013), My Panties (new editions), Proofread (2023) and some brand spanking new works. These projects have taken a small army of people + friends to make that include: photographers, fabricators, videographers, carpenters, technicians, a horse, mushroom experts, natural dyers, performers, pattern cutters, stitchers, ceramists, printmakers, sound engineers and a dog.

Drop on by and say hi üëã 

‚Ä¢ 5pm till 8pm (with remarks at 6pm)
‚Ä¢ The Nickle Galleries 
‚Ä¢ Practice Pinny by Heather Leier @heatherleierart, also opens at the same time/same place!

caption.text:
I ‚ù§Ô∏èNYC!¬† Our @payingforitfilm Q&A was moderated by longtime Kensington Market T.O. friend and neighbor @jordan.tannahill now NYC-based, who led a thoughtful conversation. I was so happy to be reunited with my SHORTBUS family. Ever inspiring @johncameronmitchell ‚Äî an Exec. Producer of @payingforitfilm -- taught me well, imparting sagely advice in filmmaking with the aim of hitting "the heart, head, and funny bone." Producer Howard Gertler @hgertler & groundbreaking filmmaker @stephenwintersir .No words can describe how much it means to have grown up under their caring, sweet righteous, and hilarious influence. I love you!üíó Also wonderful to introduce Emily L√™ @emilytkle to my extended fam. Now E. knows where I come from. ü´Ç

Thank you @filmmovement  for bringing @payingforitfilm to America‚Äî Cheers to Michael, Alex, Erin and Mike. Big up to @quadcinema for helping launch us in the U.S.¬†üá®üá¶üé¨

In the early morn, Chester Brown and I travel from frozen snowy NYC to balmly L.A. üèùÔ∏èüåû. with Special Preview screenings @payingforitfilm  @laemmle_royal Tues. Feb 3rd 7:30pm¬†
@laemmleglendale Wed. Feb. 4th 7:30PM with Q&A Mod. Mae Martin @hooraymae + Special guests, PFI opens Feb 6 @laemmleglendale

I've heard it can be hard to get L.A. peeps out to the cinema, so tell your friends, fam and neighors to get their buns out to see us. üçëThanks for spreading the word! üó£Ô∏èüì£ Come Out, Come Out! ¬†

Comic book signing @theshq  Thurs. Feb. 5th 5-7PM.

Chicago Fri. Feb. 13th 6PM @filmcenter Mod. @raypride

caption.text:
This Epstein File newly released email raise red flags and the implications are troubling to say the least. Trump‚Äôs Secretary of Commerce didn‚Äôt accidentally brush past Jeffrey Epstein‚Äôs orbit, he allegedly boarded the plane, flew to the island, and brought eight children with him. Let that sink in. 

If these allegations are accurate, they lay bare the Trump administration‚Äôs moral bankruptcy in brutal clarity. The same Republicans who never shut up about law and order, about ‚Äúsaving the children,‚Äù about rooting out elite corruption, now want everyone to yawn, look away, and move on. Nah. We have read the survivors‚Äô accounts, firsthand descriptions of what was done to them as children on Little Saint James, and those testimonies are not abstract or theoretical. They are harrowing, specific, and devastating. So when documents surface alleging that Lutnick traveled to Epstein‚Äôs island and brought children with him, this is not gossip, it is an alarm bell.

caption.text:
Roger Waters‚Äô refusal to back down from his controversial remarks about the late Ozzy Osbourne continues to generate backlash, with the dispute now drawing in additional high-profile voices from the rock and metal community.

The controversy has now prompted a response from DISTURBED frontman David Draiman, who sharply criticized Waters after watching a segment of the Piers Morgan interview. Taking to social media, Draiman did not hold back in his assessment of the PINK FLOYD co-founder.

‚Äú@rogerwaters lost his humanity, if he ever had any, in a bottle of vodka many years ago,‚Äù Draiman wrote on X. ‚ÄúHe only wishes he could be as beloved, respected and admired as @OzzyOsbourne. Keep his name out of your Jew hating, dictator loving, filthy mouth.‚Äù

Read more at metaladdicts.com

#daviddraiman #rogerwaters #ozzy #ozzyosbourne #heavymetalnews #metalnews #metaladdicts
